method.name: postMessage
method.description: Causes a MessageEvent to be dispatched at the target window when any pending script that must be executed completes (e.g., remaining event handlers if window.postMessage is called from an event handler, previously-set pending timeouts, etc.). The MessageEvent has the type message, a data property which is set to the string value of the first argument provided to window.postMessage, an origin property corresponding to the origin of the main document in the window calling window.postMessage at the time window.postMessage was called, and a source property which is the window from which window.postMessage is called. (Other standard properties of events are present with their expected values.) The window object on which postMessage is called is a reference to another window; such a reference may be obtained, for example, using the contentWindow property of an iframe element, the object returned by window.open, or by named or numeric index on window.frames.

parameter.name: message
parameter.description: String data to be sent to the window.

parameter.name: targetOrigin
parameter.description: Specifies what the origin of the window object must be for the event to be dispatched, either as the literal string "*" (indicating no preference) or as a URI. If at the time the event is scheduled to be dispatched the scheme, hostname, or port of the window's document does not match that provided in targetOrigin, the event will not be dispatched; only if all three match will the event be dispatched. This mechanism provides control over where messages are sent; for example, if postMessage were used to transmit a password, it would be absolutely critical that this argument be a URI whose origin is the same as the intended receiver of the message containing the password, to prevent interception of the password by a malicious third party.

method.name: getElementsByClassName
method.description: Returns a NodeList containing all the Element nodes with the specified classNames.

parameter.name: classNames
parameter.description: A string representing the class name(s) of the elements to return. Multiple class names should be separated by spaces.

method.return-description: Returns a NodeList containing all the Element nodes with the specified classNames.
method.example:
Using getElementsByClassName

	        document.getElementsByClassName("question");

Would return a NodeList of all elements in the document to which the class "question" applies.

	        document.getElementsByClassName("question issue");

Would return a NodeList of all elements in the document to which both the classes "question" and "issue" apply.
method.remarks: Returns a list of elements in the document to which the specified className applies. The returned NodeList is sorted in tree order (the order the elements were found during a depth-first preorder traversal through the node tree).

method.name: getElementsByClassName
method.description: Returns a NodeList containing all the Element nodes with the specified classNames.

parameter.name: classNames
parameter.description: A string representing the class name(s) of the elements to return. Multiple class names should be separated by spaces.

method.return-description: Returns a NodeList containing all the Element nodes with the specified classNames.
method.example:
Using getElementsByClassName

	                    document.getElementById("useCases").getElementsByClassName("question");

Would return a NodeList of all elements inside the element with the id "useCases" to which the class "question" applies.

	                    document.getElementById("useCases").getElementsByClassName("question issue");

Would return a NodeList of all elements inside the element with the id "useCases" to which both the classes "question" and "issue" apply.
method.remarks: Returns a list of child elements to which the specified className applies. The returned NodeList is sorted in tree order (the order the elements were found during a depth-first preorder traversal through the node tree).

property.description: Allows the user to indicate that a control is to be focused as soon as the page is loaded, allowing the user to just start typing without having to manually focus the main control.

property.name: challenge
property.description: Specifies the challenge attribute for the keygen.

property.name: disabled
property.description: Specifies whether the element is disabled.

property.name: form
property.description: Specifies the associated form element.

property.name: keytype
property.description: An enumerated attribute that specifies the keytype.

property.name: name
property.description: Specifies the name of the keygen.

property.name: willValidate
property.description: Specifies whether the element will be validated when the form is submitted.

property.name: validity
property.description: Specifies the validity of the element.

property.name: validationMessage
property.description: Specifies a suitably localized message that the user agent would show the user if this were the only form control with a validity constraint problem.

method.name: checkValidity
method.description: The user agent must instanceally validate the constraints of the form element, and return true if the constraint validation return a positive result, and false if it returned a negative result.

method.name: setCustomValidity
method.description: Sets the custom validity error message to the value of the given message argument.

parameter.name: error
parameter.description: The error message for the validity check.

class.description: Represents a caption in the user interface.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLLabelElement.

property.name: form
property.description: Return the form owner of the element.

property.name: htmlFor
property.description: Indicates a form control with which the caption is to be associated.

property.name: control
property.description: Returns the form control that is associated with this element.

class.description: Represents a caption for the rest of the contents of the legend element's parent fieldset element, if any.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLLegendElement.

property.name: form
property.description: Returns the form owner of the element, if any, or null otherwise.

class.description: Represents a list item.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLLIElement.

property.name: value
property.description: A valid integer giving the ordinal value of the list item.

class.description: Allows authors to link their document to other resources.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLLinkElement.

property.name: disabled
property.description: Specifies whether the link element is disabled.

property.name: href
property.description: Specifies the destination of the link elements.

property.name: rel
property.description: Specifies the types of link indicated.

property.name: relList
property.description: Specifies a list of the rel attribute.

property.name: media
property.description: Specifies which media the resource applies to.

property.name: hreflang
property.description: Specifies the language of the linked resource.

property.name: type
property.description: Specifies the MIME type of the linked resource.

property.name: sizes
property.description: Specifies the sizes for the assiciated icon elements.

class.description: In conjunction with any area element decsendants, defines an image map.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLMapElement.

property.name: name
property.description: Specifies the name of a map.

property.name: areas
property.description: Returns an HTMLCollection of the area elements in the map.

property.name: images
property.description: Returns an HTMLCollection of the img and object elements that use the map.

class.description: Represents a list of commands.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLMenuElement.

property.name: type
property.description: Specifies the kind of menu being declared.

property.name: label
property.description: Specifies the label for the menu.

class.description: Represents various kinds of metadata that cannot be expressed using the title,base,link,style, and script elements.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLMetaElement.

property.name: name
property.description: Specifies the name for the metadata.

property.name: httpEquiv
property.description: Specifies a pragma directive used for the meta element.

property.name: content
property.description: Specifies the content for the metadata.

class.description: Represents a scalar measurement within a known range, or a fractional value; for example disk usage, the relevance of a query result, or the fraction of a voting population to have selected a particular candidate.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLMeterElement.

property.name: value
property.description: Specifies the value to have the gauge indicate as the "measured" value.

property.name: min
property.description: Specifies the lower bound of the range.

property.name: max
property.description: Specifies the upper bound of the range.

property.name: low
property.description: Specifies the range that is considered to be the "low" part.

property.name: high
property.description: Specifies the range that is considered to be the "high" part.

property.name: optimum
property.description: Specifies the position that is "optimum".

property.name: form
property.description: Used to explicitly associate the meter element with its form owner.

property.name: labels
property.description: Returns a NodeList of all the label elements that the form control is associated with.

class.description: Represent an external resource, which, depending on the type of the resource, will either be treated as an image, as a nested browsing context, or as an external resource to be processed by a plugin.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLObjectElement.

property.name: data
property.description: Specifies the address of the resource.

property.name: type
property.description: Specifies the type of the resource.

property.name: name
property.description: Specifies the name of the nested browsing context.

property.name: useMap
property.description: Indicates whether the object has an associated image map.

property.name: form
property.description: Used to associate the object with its form owner.

property.name: width
property.description: Specifies the width attribute.

property.name: height
property.description: Specifies the height attribute.

property.name: contentDocument
property.description: Returns the Document object of the active document of the object element's nested browsing context, if it has one; otherwise, it must return null.

property.name: contentWindow
property.description: Return the WindowProxy object of the object element's nested browsing context, if it has one; otherwise, it must return null.

property.name: willValidate
property.description: Specifies whether the element will be validated when the form is submitted.

property.name: validity
property.description: Specifies the validity of the element.

property.name: validationMessage
property.description: Specifies a suitably localized message that the user agent would show the user if this were the only form control with a validity constraint problem.

method.name: checkValidity
method.description: The user agent must instanceally validate the constraints of the form element, and return true if the constraint validation return a positive result, and false if it returned a negative result.

method.name: setCustomValidity
method.description: Sets the custom validity error message to the value of the given message argument.

parameter.name: error
parameter.description: The error message for the validity check.

class.description: Represent a list of items, where the items have been intentionally ordered, such that changing the order would change the meaning of the document.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLOListElement.

property.name: reversed
property.description: Specifies whether list is a descending list.

property.name: start
property.description: Specifies the original value of the first item.

class.description: Represent a group of option elements with a common label.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLOptGroupElement.

property.name: disabled
property.description: Used to disable a group of option elements together.

property.name: label
property.description: Specifies the name of the group, for the purposes of the user interface.

class.description: Represent the result of a calculation.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLOutputElement.

property.name: htmlFor
property.description: Allows an explicit relationship to be made between the result of a calculation and the elements that represent the values that went into the calculation or that otherwise influenced the calculation.

property.name: form
property.description: Used to explicitly associate the output element with its form owner.

property.name: name
property.description: Specifies the name of the output element.

property.name: type
property.description: Returns the string "output".

property.name: defaultValue
property.description: Returns the element's current default value.

property.name: value
property.description: Acts like the element's textContent IDL attribute, except that on setting, in addition, before the child nodes are changed, the element's value mode flag must be set to value.

property.name: willValidate
property.description: Specifies whether the element will be validated when the form is submitted.

property.name: validity
property.description: Specifies the validity of the element.

property.name: validationMessage
property.description: Specifies a suitably localized message that the user agent would show the user if this were the only form control with a validity constraint problem.

method.name: checkValidity
method.description: The user agent must instanceally validate the constraints of the form element, and return true if the constraint validation return a positive result, and false if it returned a negative result.

method.name: setCustomValidity
method.description: Sets the custom validity error message to the value of the given message argument.

parameter.name: error
parameter.description: The error message for the validity check.

class.description: Defines parameters for plugins invoked by object elements.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLParamElement.

property.name: name
property.description: Specifies the name of the parameter.

property.name: value
property.description: Specifies the value of the parameter.

class.description: Represents the completion progress of a task.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLProgressElement.

property.name: value
property.description: Specifies how much of the task has been completed.

property.name: max
property.description: Specifies how much work the task requires in total.

property.name: position
property.description: For a determinate progress bar (one with known current and maximum values), returns the result of dividing the current value by the maximum value.

property.name: form
property.description: Used to explicitly associate the progress element with its form owner.

property.name: labels
property.description: Returns a NodeList of all the label elements that the form control is associated with.

class.description: Allows authors to include dynamic script and data blocks in their documents.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLScriptElement.

property.name: src
property.description: Specifies the address of the external script resource to use.

property.name: async
property.description: Specifies whether the script should be run asynchronously.

property.name: defer
property.description: Specifies whether the script is executed when the page has finished parsing.

property.name: type
property.description: Specifies the language of the script or format of the data.

property.name: charset
property.description: Specifies the character encoding of the external script resource.

property.name: text
property.description: Returns the contents of the element, ignoring child nodes that aren't text nodes.

class.description: Allows authors to specify multiple alternative media resources for media elements.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLSourceElement.

property.name: src
property.description: Specifies the address of the media resource.

property.name: type
property.description: Specifies the type of the media resource.

property.name: media
property.description: Specifies the intended media type of the media resource, to help the user agent determine if this media resource is useful to the user before fetching it.

class.description: Allows authors to embed style information in their documents.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLStyleElement.

property.name: disabled
property.description: Specifies whether the style element is disabled.

property.name: media
property.description: Specifies which media the styles apply to.

property.name: type
property.description: Specifies the styling language.

property.name: scoped
property.description: Indicates whether the styles are intended just for the subtree rooted at the style element's parent element, as opposed to the whole Document.

class.description: Represents a block of rows that consist of a body of data for the parent table element, if the tbody element has a parent and it is a table.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLTableSelectionElement.

property.name: rows
property.description: Returns an HTMLCollection of the tr elements of the table section.

method.name: insertRow
method.description: Creates a tr element, inserts it into the table section at the position given by the argument, and returns the tr.

parameter.name: index
parameter.description: The index where the row will be inserted.

method.name: deleteRow
method.description: Removes the tr element with the given position in the table section.

parameter.name: index
parameter.description: The index of the row to be deleted.

class.description: Represents a header cell in a table.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLTableHeaderCellElement.

property.name: scope
property.description: Specifies the scope of the table header element.

class.description: Represents either a time on a 24 hour clock, or a precise date in the proleptic Gregorian calendar, optionally with a time and a time-zone offset.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLTimeElement.

property.name: dateTime
property.description: Gives the date or time being specified.

property.name: pubDate
property.description: Indicates that the date and time given by the element is the publication date and time of the nearest ancestor article element, or, if the element has no ancestor article element, of the document as a whole.

property.name: valueAsDate
property.description: Returns a Date object representing the specified date and time.

class.description: Represents the name or title of a document.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLTitleElement.

property.name: text
property.description: Returns the contents of the element, ignoring child nodes that are not text nodes.

class.description: Represents an element used for playing videos or movies.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLVideoElement.

property.name: width
property.description: Determines the width of the video element.

property.name: height
property.description: Determines the height of the video element.

property.name: videoWidth
property.description: Returns the intrinsic width of the video in CSS pixels.

property.name: videoHeight
property.description: Returns the intrinsic height of the video in CSS pixels.

property.name: poster
property.description: Gives the address of an image file that the user agent can show while no video data is available.

class.description: Force a line break.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLBRElement.

property.name: clear
property.description: Control flow of text around floats. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

class.description: Generic block container.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLDivElement.

property.name: align
property.description: Horizontal text alignment. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

class.description: Definition List.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLDListElement.

property.name: compact
property.description: Reduce spacing between list items. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

class.description: For the H1 to H6 elements.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLHeadingElement.

property.name: align
property.description: Horizontal text alignment. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

class.description: Create a horizontal rule.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLHRElement.

property.name: align
property.description: Align the rule on the page. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

property.name: noShade
property.description: Indicates to the user agent that there should be no shading in the rendering of this element. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

property.name: size
property.description: The height of the rule. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

property.name: width
property.description: The width of the rule. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

class.description: Root of an HTML document.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLhtmlElement.

property.name: version
property.description: Version information about the document's DTD. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

class.description: Specifies an element for paragraphs.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLParagraphElement.

property.name: align
property.description: Horizontal line alignment. This property is depricated in HTML 5.

class.description: Preformatted text.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLPreElement.

property.name: width
property.description: Fixed width for content. This property is depricated in HTML 5.

class.description: Specifies a span element used to surround content blocks for formatting.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLSpanElement.

class.description: Represents a data cell in a table.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLTableDataCellElement.

class.description: Represents a list of items, where the order of the items is not important.

constructor.description: Creates an instance of the HTMLUListElement.

property.name: compact
property.description: Reduce spacing between list items. This property has been removed in HTML 5.

property.name: type
property.description: The style of the list. This property has been removed in HTML 5.
